<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-05-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-05-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="98" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d98">
                    <head>Louis and Casimir Didett</head>
                    <note rend="inline" rendition="#center" type="source">[Translation.]</note>
                    <dateline>
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nimes</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-05-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 3, 1865</date>.</dateline>
                    <p rend="flushleft">
                        <hi rend="italic">To the United States Minister in Paris:</hi>
                    </p>
                    <p>We have the honor of transmitting to you in this envelope the address of our
                        house, on the occasion of the death of the great American citizen, whom we
                        and the whole world lament.</p>
                    <pb facs="0138" n="66" xml:id="pg_66"/>
                    <p>We join in this universal manifestation of sorrow, and ask you to send our
                        homage to its address.</p>
                    <p>Receive the respectful greeting of your very humble servants,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>LOUIS &amp; CASIMIR DIDETT,</signed>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Father and son, hat manufacturers in Nimes</hi>.</closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>